data.title: Zygmunt Vetulani (diplomat)
data.text:
Polish diplomat and economist

Zygmunt Michał Vetulani (1894–1942) was a Polish diplomat and economist. He was a general consul of Rzeczpospolita in Kaliningrad, Baghdad and Rio de Janeiro.

Biography

[edit]

He was the oldest son of Roman Vetulani and Elżbieta Kunachowicz. His brothers were Kazimierz, Tadeusz and Adam. He also had two sisters: Maria and Elżbieta. In 1912 he graduated Queen Sophia high school in Sanok.[1]

He was married to Stanisława Leśniewska. They had a daughter, Wanda.
